Dr. Brennan
Brennan博士

15
00:00:45,890 --> 00:00:46,490
Yes.
是的

16
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:48,240
I'm Ian Dyson with the NTSB.
我是NTSB的lan Dyson

17
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:50,570
This is my assistant,Zack Addy.
这是我的助手Zack Addy

18
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:54,150
At approximately 0400 last night,
昨晚大约凌晨4点的时候

19
00:00:54,260 --> 00:00:58,240
a private jet with five passengers on board reported horizontal stabilizer trouble
一架载着5位乘客的私人飞机报告说 水平尾翼出了问题

20
00:00:58,350 --> 00:01:01,000
200 miles southeast of Norfolk.
在Norfole东南200英里

21
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:03,390
Yeager Airport in Charleston tracked them for 30 minutes
Charleston的Yeager机场人员 追踪了他们30分钟

22
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,700
until they dropped off the radar screen at 0430.
直到他们4点30分从雷达中消失

23
00:01:06,850 --> 00:01:08,980
The plane tried to make an emergency landing here
这飞机试着在这儿紧急迫降

24
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:11,990
when it clipped some trees and slammed to the ground.
它撞倒了一些树然后撞到了地面

25
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:15,330
We found another mostly intact body over near the trees.
我们在那边树的附近发现了 一具几乎完整的尸体

26
00:01:15,550 --> 00:01:17,510
The rest is bits and pieces.
其他的就残缺不全了

27
00:01:17,590 --> 00:01:19,330
What makes this one of our cases?
这为什么成了我们的案子？

28
00:01:19,410 --> 00:01:20,080
I beg your pardon?
你说什么？

29
00:01:20,210 --> 00:01:24,570
We're kind of special. We're elite.We don't sort through just any set of bodies.
我们有点特别, 是精英分子 不是任何尸体都需要我们出手

30
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:27,770
It was a State Department flight with a bunch of VIPs on board.
这是一趟州政府部门的航班 上面有很多贵宾

31
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,270
Is that special enough?
那够特别了吗?

32
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:31,110
I apologize if I've offended you.
如果冒犯了你, 我道歉

33
00:01:31,220 --> 00:01:35,090
Usually,we have an FBI agent who mediates our interpersonal encounters.
通常，我们有一位处理这些 人际交往的FBI探员

34
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:36,690
We found another skull.
我们找到了另一片头骨

35
00:01:36,950 --> 00:01:40,150
Two skulls.Those,uh,pieces are from two different skulls.
两片头骨, 嗯, 那是两片不同来源的头骨 

36
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:43,320
I'll leave you super elite types to it.
那就让你们这些超级精英去测定吧

37
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:50,390
Zack,we don't need Booth to mediate our interpersonal encounters.
Zack, 我们不需要Booth来处理人际交往

38
00:01:50,510 --> 00:01:54,570
Pilot,copilot,brings our count to six.
驾驶员，副驾驶，算来遇难者有6个了

39
00:01:54,770 --> 00:02:00,660
Three mostly intact sets of remains,one partial and two fragmented.
有三具几乎完整，一具部分完整 另两具零散不堪

40
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:03,000
Obviously,bodies are burned to a crisp.
很明显，尸体已经烧焦了

41
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:09,310
No dermis,very little soft tissue,indications of high-impact trauma;
体无完肤，剩有非常少的软组织， 受到过高强度的打击伤害 

42
00:02:09,450 --> 00:02:12,500
burst fracture of the lower thoracic and lumbar vertebrae consistent
下胸椎和腰椎骨的爆裂性骨折

43
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:16,120
with injuries caused by the vertical impact of the falling aircraft.
与飞机掉落的垂直撞击引起的伤害一致

44
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:19,880
Should I keep talking as though you're paying attention?
我要假装你在听,继续说下去吗?

45
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,090
What do you make of this?
你觉得这是什么？

46
00:02:26,420 --> 00:02:28,070
A femur fragment.
一片大腿骨碎片

47
00:02:28,260 --> 00:02:29,570
No charring.
没有烧焦

48
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,920
You think this fragment doesn't belong to the plane crash.
你认为这碎片不是飞机上的

49
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:33,320
What are the odds?
这可能性有多大?

50
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:36,520
A crashing plane falling  directly on a human being?
一驾坠落的飞机直接撞到一个人身上?

51
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:41,700
One in... ten million.
千万分之一的概率

52
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:46,540
The information that I'm about to tell you must not leave this room.
我现在要告诉你们的消息绝对要保密

53
00:02:46,650 --> 00:02:49,900
I am philosophically opposed to institutional secrecy in all its forms.
我基本上反对任何形式的保密机制

54
00:02:50,010 --> 00:02:52,210
Fine. Get out.
好, 出去

55
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:56,330
Two Communist Chinese trade attaches were on that plane
当它坠毁时, 有两位中国共产党 贸易大使馆人员在那架飞机上

56
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:58,760
when it crashed--both high-ranking in party 
两个人在党内都是高层人士 

57
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,570
Well,obviously,we shot it down.
哦, 很明显, 是我们击落它的

58
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:04,000
The FAA and the NTSB can prove that it was an accident.
FAA和NTSB都能证明那是一场意外

59
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:07,180
Also on the manifest was an American businessman,
而且，在旅客名单上还有一个美国商人

60
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:10,470
a pilot and a copilot.Five people.
驾驶员和副驾驶, 共5个人

61
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:14,940
Dr. Goodman,we found six sets of human remains on that airplane.
Goodman博士, 我们在飞机上发现了 6具人体残骸

62
00:03:15,010 --> 00:03:18,030
Not to mention three bone fragments which were not on the plane.
何况还有三块骨头碎片不是飞机上的

63
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:20,160
Is there any chance those bone fragments were on the plane?
有没有可能那些骨头碎片是飞机上的?

64
00:03:20,350 --> 00:03:21,930
What,you mean as carry-on luggage?
什么，你是说像行李一样?

65
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:25,180
No,everything on the plane burned.They were untouched by fire.
不，飞机上的所有东西都被烧了 它们却没有

66
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:28,140
And forget about the bone fragments for the time being.
先别管那些骨头碎片了

67
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:32,740
The State Department is extremely anxious to find the identity of that 6th person.
州政府部门非常迫切的想知道机上 第6个人的身份

68
00:03:32,870 --> 00:03:35,220
No one wishes this to become an international incident,
没人想让这成为一个国际性事件

69
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:38,680
therefore this is our only priority.
因此这是我们必须先要做的

70
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,340
I disagree.
我不同意

71
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,880
For the love of God,why?
上帝啊, 为什么?

72
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,780
Because the plane crash was an accident,bone fragments were not.
因为这架飞机失事是个意外 而骨头碎片不是

73
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:46,670
How do you know?
你怎么知道？

74
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:48,600
Zack found unusual cut marks.
Zack发现不寻常的切割痕迹

75
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:51,560
Cut marks congruent with dismemberment.
切割痕迹与肢解形成的一致

76
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:56,340
People,one hour ago,I received a call from the Secretary of State requesting
伙计们，一小时前我收到了 国务卿打来的电话

77
00:03:56,460 --> 00:04:00,940
that the unidentified extra passenger be our first priority.
要求确认不明旅客的身份为当务之急

78
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:04,070
So,now politics are more important than murder?
因此，现在政治比谋杀更重要?

79
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:07,830
I'm not saying "please."I'm not being reasonable.I'm making the decision.
我不是在说"请"，我也不是要理智 我是在做决定

80
00:04:07,990 --> 00:04:13,350
First and foremost,identify that six body.
首要而且是最重要的任务是 确定第6个人的身份

81
00:04:20,690 --> 00:04:23,670
Got it,or you want me to explain again?
明白了, 还是要我再解释一遍?

82
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:27,630
I got it,okay?The plane goes down,kablooey.There's an extra body on board which
我明白了, 好了吧? 飞机出毛病掉了下来 多了一具尸体你却不真的在乎

83
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:30,980
you really don't care about 'cause you're more interested in these bone
是因为你对这些在地上

84
00:04:31,150 --> 00:04:32,580
fragments that you found on the ground.
找到的尸骨更有兴趣

85
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:33,980
Exactly.
正是

86
00:04:34,090 --> 00:04:36,010
Oh,this all you got?
噢，这就是所有你找到的?

87
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:40,870
So far.Piece of skull,chunk of vertebrae,part of a femur.
目前为止是的, 一片头盖骨碎片 一大块椎骨，一部分大腿骨

88
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:41,740
Not much to go on.
不够继续调查啊

89
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:44,380
These fragments come from a person who was hacked.
这些碎片来自一个被肢解的人

90
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:45,470
Hacked to little bits?
被肢解成小碎片?

91
00:04:45,590 --> 00:04:49,320
No,medium-size bits.I'm not sure how it turned into little bits yet.
不，中等大小的碎片 我现在还不清楚它是怎么变成小碎片的

92
00:04:49,470 --> 00:04:51,130
Okay,and I'm here why?
好的, 那我为什么到这来?

93
00:04:51,350 --> 00:04:54,500
Dismemberment,little bits--it's a murder.
肢解成小块，这是谋杀

94
00:04:54,690 --> 00:04:57,180
FBI doesn't have jurisdiction at a golf course.
FBI对高尔夫球场可没有管辖权限

95
00:04:57,300 --> 00:05:00,240
--Well,who does? --I don't know.Try the PGA.
--那谁有? --我不知道, PGA(职业高尔夫球协会)吧

96
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:04,120
You know,you've done a couple cases without me and you miss me.
你知道的，你已经有好几个案子 没和我一起办了, 想我了吧

97
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:05,780
Zack misses you,not me.
Zack想你了，我可没有

98
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:07,000
Zack and I don't even talk.
Zack和我甚至没怎么说过话

99
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:09,280
He seems to think it's a male-bonding ritual.
他似乎觉得这是男人之间的默契

100
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:10,030
Maybe he's right.
可能他对了

101
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:11,200
--No,it's not. --Could be.
- 不，才不是 - 有可能

102
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,900
You told him that so you wouldn't have to talk to him.
你和他那样说, 所以你就不必和他说话了

103
00:05:12,970 --> 00:05:15,280
Well,it was nicer than shooting him.
那总比开枪打他要好吧

104
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:19,040
Goodman has ordered me to investigate the other extra body.
Goodman已经命令我去调查那一具 多出来的尸体

105
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:21,300
Well,then you better get on that.Next time you know you miss me,
那你最好马上去做, 下次想我时

106
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:23,650
pick up the phone,call me.We'll do lunch or something.
拿起电话，打给我 我们可以一起吃午餐或是干点别的

107
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:24,330
I do not miss you.
我才没想你

108
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:26,850
--Come on. Say it! --I do not miss you!
- 得了吧, 说出来吧 - 我才没想你!

109
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,900
Dr. Brennan,Agent Booth,you have a visitor.
Brennan博士，Booth先生 有人找你们

110
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:32,800
--No,I don't. --Miss me.
- 不，我才没想你 - 你有想我

111
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,020
Dr. Temperance Brennan.
Temperance Brennan 博士

112
00:05:40,170 --> 00:05:40,810
Yes.
是的

113
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,100
Special Agent Seeley Booth. I'm Jesse Caine.
Seeley Booth特别探员 我叫Jesse Caine

114
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:44,170
You're Jesse Caine?
你是Jesse Caine?

115
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,070
You've heard of me?
你听说过我?

116
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,340
I haven't.
我没有

117
00:05:46,410 --> 00:05:49,050
Jesse here is sort of an expert on missing persons cases.
这儿的Jesse是失踪案的专家

118
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:53,080
I've done some writing on missing person laws and investigative techniques.
我写了一些失踪人口方面的法案 和调查方法的文章

119
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:57,090
Interagency cooperation,jurisdictional dispute,that kind of thing.
部门间合作，司法纠纷 诸如此类的东西

120
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:59,260
I heard about the bones you found at the golf course.
我听说了你们在高尔夫球场 发现尸骨的事

121
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:01,520
I can't really talk about that.
我不能和你谈论这个

122
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,580
I don't mean the Communist Chinese on the plane.
我不是指飞机上的中国共产党人

123
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:05,580
Communist Chinese?
中国共产党人?

124
00:06:05,850 --> 00:06:08,520
The other bones,the fragments.
其余的骨块，那些碎片

125
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,640
How'd you hear about the Communist Chinese?
你是怎么听说中国共产党人的?

126
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:13,720
Those pieces of bone you found on the golf course?
那些你在高尔夫球场发现的碎片?

127
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:17,330
I'm pretty sure that's my dad.
我很确定那是我爸爸

128
00:06:50,330 --> 00:06:54,590
My expertise in missing persons investigation derives from one thing
我这些寻找失踪人员的能力 源于一件事

129
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,340
my search for my father.
寻找我父亲

130
00:06:56,570 --> 00:07:00,350
He went missing five years ago during a trip to his cottage in Virginia Beach.
他五年前在去弗吉尼亚海滩别墅途中失踪

131
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:03,180
What makes you think these bone fragments come from your father?
是什么使你认为这些碎片是你父亲的呢?

132
00:07:03,250 --> 00:07:06,510
You know there is a question of national security here that is in my jurisdiction.
这儿有一个关于国家安全的问题 是在我的管辖之内

133
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:08,530
He's not supposed to know about the Chinese.
他不应该知道中国人的事

134
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:09,940
My investigations lead me to conclude
我的调查让我得出结论

135
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:13,350
that my father was murdered in the area and his body disposed.
我父亲被谋杀并抛尸在这地方  

136
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:14,450
What do the police say?
警察怎么认为?

137
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,630
They gave up four years ago.
他们四年前就放弃了

138
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,860
Because there was no evidence of foul play.
因为没有证据表明那是犯罪事件

139
00:07:17,970 --> 00:07:21,180
The investigation was bungled.The city police didn't have the manpower.
调查搞砸了 城里警察没有足够的人手

140
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:23,060
The state trooper said it was a federal matter
州警察说那是联邦政府的事

141
00:07:23,140 --> 00:07:25,580
and you guys suggested a private investigator.
而你们建议私人调查

142
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:29,270
It was not bungled,okay?Because there was no evidence of foul play.
那没有被搞砸，好吗? 因为没有证据表明那是犯罪事件

143
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,590
It's a common story,okay?
这是很寻常的事，好吧？

144
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,240
A guy goes in for a pack of cigarettes,
一个男人去买一包烟

145
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:35,560
he ends up renting out snorkeling gear in Guam.
最后却租借了关岛的齿轮通气管

146
00:07:35,870 --> 00:07:39,630
He doesn't know what it's like to lose a parent. You do.
他根本不知道失去父母是什么滋味 而你知道

147
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:41,890
You want back down a jot there,buddy?
你最好收回刚才说的话，伙计?

148
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,460
How do you know about that?
你是怎么知道的?

149
00:07:43,530 --> 00:07:46,670
No offense,Dr. Brennan,but you're a writer,a well-known scientist.
没有冒犯的意思，Brennan博士 但是你是个作家，一个知名科学家

150
00:07:46,790 --> 00:07:48,700
It's out there. Plus,you're one of us.
大家都知道, 另外, 你是我们中的一员

151
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:49,410
One of us?
我们中的一员？

152
00:07:49,490 --> 00:07:52,520
People whose loved ones have simply vanished.In your case,both parents.
人们所爱的人就那么消失了 而你则失去了双亲

153
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,510
Okay,how do you know about the Chinese?
好吧，你是怎么知道中国人的事的?

154
