是的，而且在这块腿骨有唇形变 (骨的病变)和发亮的痕迹

197
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:16,890
Arthritis?
关节炎?

198
00:10:16,970 --> 00:10:18,340
So,middle-aged guy.
那么，是个中年男人

199
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:20,730
Weathering and discoloration suggests these bones have been
风化和退色表明这些骨块已经

200
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:24,210
out there for approximately five years.
在那大约有5年了

201
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:27,600
I'm going to ask you guys to help me on this.
我想让你们帮我一下

202
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,540
You mean,after the communist thing?
你指, 处理完共产党人的事之后?

203
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:31,610
No,immediately.
不, 马上

204
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:32,550
I'm in.
我加入

205
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:34,210
You want us to defy Dr. Goodman?
你想让我们违抗Goodman博士吗?

206
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:34,930
I'm in.
我加入

207
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:39,980
Not defy,per se.Do both jobs,but...but keep one a secret.
不是违抗, 应该说是两件事情同时进行 但一件保密

208
00:10:40,090 --> 00:10:40,880
I'm in.
我加入

209
00:10:40,990 --> 00:10:42,430
We get it. You're a rebel.
我们知道了，你是个反叛者

210
00:10:42,540 --> 00:10:45,180
Zack,I need you  to analyze the cuts on the bone.
Zack，我要你分析一下骨头上的割痕

211
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:46,730
I was kind of hoping to keep my job.
我只是希望能保住工作

212
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:50,420
There's not enough skull here for me to do any reconstruction.
这儿没有足够的头盖骨让我进行重组

213
00:10:50,530 --> 00:10:53,810
If I give you a picture,you could tell me if the skull piece doesn't match?
如果我给你张照片，你能告诉 我这些头盖骨是否匹配吗?

214
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:55,530
I could construct a schematic and
我可以建个示意图

215
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:59,470
see if the shard fit the general shape of the skull if I had a picture.
来看那些碎片是否匹配头骨的大概形状 如果有照片的话

216
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:03,650
Has anyone noticed that I was the first to offer help and apparently,I'm useless
有谁注意我是第一个愿意提供帮助的人 而显然，我没事做

217
00:11:03,770 --> 00:11:07,800
Not true.You're the one that's going to keep Goodman from finding out.
不是的，你负责不要让Goodman 发现我们的调查

218
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:09,490
I'm in.
我加入

219
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:13,240
So the bone fragments are the same sex and age as my father.
这些骨片与我父亲的性别和年龄相符

220
00:11:13,430 --> 00:11:14,000
Yes.
是的

221
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:15,200
Thank you.
谢谢

222
00:11:15,470 --> 00:11:17,690
It's a long way from conclusive.
还要很久才能断定是不是你父亲

223
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:20,390
Yeah,I know at times like these not to get hopeful.
对，我知道像现在这时候不要充满希望

224
00:11:20,470 --> 00:11:22,840
But,on the other hand,you've got to have hope.
但是，另一方面，你必须有希望

225
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:24,810
Even after five years?
即使5年以后?

226
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,000
People are found after decades,Dr. Brennan.
有些人数十年后才被发现，Brennan博士

227
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:29,640
After centuries.You've done some of the finding.
甚至是几个世纪后 而你已经有所发现了

228
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:33,390
Booth says you've made a living off of the disappearance of your father.
Booth说自你父亲失踪后 你就靠追踪他生活

229
00:11:34,530 --> 00:11:36,970
About six months after my father disappeared,
我父亲失踪大约6个月后

230
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:39,580
I found out nobody was actually looking for him.
我发现实际上根本没人在找他

231
00:11:39,660 --> 00:11:43,050
Next thing I knew,I was an expert in motivating the police-- victims' rights.
然后，我就变成了个推动警察 保护受害者权力的专家

232
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:47,690
Becoming well-known is a byproduct of my search for my father,not the goal of my search.
变成名只是我寻找父亲的副产品 并不是我寻找的目的

233
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:51,080
You should understand my motivation better than most people in law enforcement.
你应该比司法部门的人更了解我的动机

234
00:11:51,190 --> 00:11:56,000
I'm not really interested in bonding over the loss of my parents.
我没兴趣在父母失去这件事上和你有联系

235
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:59,120
Booth is looking over your file now.
Booth现在正在找你的档案

236
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:01,310
I wasn't looking for his help.
我没有寻找他的帮忙

237
00:12:01,460 --> 00:12:05,780
We work together.Booth knows that the bone fragments are evidence of foul play.
我们在一起工作，Booth知道 那些骨片是犯罪行为的证据

238
00:12:05,890 --> 00:12:08,200
That's all the motivation he needed.
那就是他所要的动机

239
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:11,030
You didn't have to lean on him?
你不必偏袒他?

240
00:12:11,530 --> 00:12:14,890
Not at all.
根本没有

241
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:17,900
If you say so.
如果你这么说的话

242
00:12:29,220 --> 00:12:33,470
One of the bone fragments has distinctive  ridge-mark indentations.
这些骨块中一块有明显的隆起缺口

243
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,600
A knife mark.
一处刀痕

244
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,300
Yes. Specifically,a carving knife.
对，具体点是，一把雕刻刀

245
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:39,430
Well,what about the other ones?The jagged marks?
其他的呢? 那个锯齿形痕迹?

246
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,790
Some kind of machine blade.
一种机器的刀锋

247
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:46,200
What? Like a... a jigsaw or a chain saw?
什么? 像是...一把竖锯或是链锯?

248
00:12:46,590 --> 00:12:50,830
Are you suggesting one of the Chinese diplomats was wielding a chain saw
你是说一个中国外交官挥舞着一把链锯?

249
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:55,770
good one,sir.Very droll.
很好，先生, 非常滑稽

250
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,790
Zack knows much more about this than I do,
Zack在这方面比我知道的要多

251
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:00,710
but we weren't discussing a literal chain saw cut,
但我们不是在讨论一个链锯割痕

252
00:13:00,870 --> 00:13:03,950
but,rather,the pattern  it leaves on the bone.
而是那链锯留在骨头上的样式

253
00:13:04,220 --> 00:13:06,690
Right?Zack?
对吧? Zack?

254
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:09,360
You know,blades move in several distinctive ways.
刀锋在骨头上有一些独特的移动方式

255
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:10,860
Several distinctive ways.
一些独特的方式

256
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,300
Circular,elliptical,segmente
圆形的，椭圆形的，线形的

257
00:13:12,380 --> 00:13:14,150
Chain saws are designed to cut soft materials at high speed.
链锯是用来在高速下切割软材料的

258
00:13:14,270 --> 00:13:16,200
When cutting hard materials like bone,they create wave-ridge walls
当切割硬物像骨头时，就会留下 由于刀锋的运动

259
00:13:16,310 --> 00:13:19,140
by the action of the blade.This pattern's too organized. Too linear.
所留下的波浪型痕迹 这个样式太整齐了, 太线形了

260
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:23,320
Therefore,no Chinese Chain Saw Massacre scenario.
因此，没有什么中国链锯杀人狂

261
00:13:24,210 --> 00:13:28,050
Yes. Fascinating.What has it go to do with the OXcts of the plane crash?
是的，令人惊奇 这和飞机失事有什么关系?

262
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:31,360
We not only have to reassemble each of the plane crash victims,
我们不仅要重组每个飞机遇难者的尸体

